// EXPECTED: compile error
// A global uN initialized with integer arithmetic is rejected: `1000 + 500` is
// typed u32, and u32 -> u21 is a narrowing conversion. This narrowing rejection
// (together with the "does not fit" check on over-width literals and C's
// constant-initializer requirement, which blocks uN-operand arithmetic) is what
// makes width-masking unnecessary at global scope: no over-width value can reach
// a global uN in the first place. emit_intn_mask therefore runs only on the
// function-body paths (IR_BINOP / IR_UNOP), where real uN arithmetic occurs.
//
// TRIPWIRE: if this ever COMPILES (someone relaxes the uN narrowing/const-fold
// rules), the global emit path must mask the result to the width at that time —
// otherwise the global would hold an unmasked over-width value. Do not delete
// this test without adding that mask.
u21 g = 1000 + 500;
u32 main() { return 0; }
